{\footnote # IDH_RUST_13}
{\footnote $ Rust - Concurrence et asynchrone}
{\footnote K Rust concurrence asynchrone;thread spawn;Arc Mutex;Send Sync;mpsc channel;async await;Future;tokio async-std smol embassy;join select}
\b\fs24 Concurrence et asynchrone \b0\fs20\par
\par
13.1 Threads OS\par
\par
{\f1   use std::thread;}\par
{\f1   let h = thread::spawn(|| \{}\par
{\f1       println!("dans le thread");}\par
{\f1       42}\par
{\f1   \});}\par
{\f1   let r = h.join().unwrap();}\par
\par
13.2 Partage de donnees\par
\par
{\f1   use std::sync::\{Arc, Mutex\};}\par
{\f1   let compteur = Arc::new(Mutex::new(0));}\par
{\f1   let handles: Vec<_> = (0..10).map(|_| \{}\par
{\f1       let c = Arc::clone(&compteur);}\par
{\f1       thread::spawn(move || \{ *c.lock().unwrap() += 1; \})}\par
{\f1   \}).collect();}\par
{\f1   for h in handles \{ h.join().unwrap(); \}}\par
\par
Send : valeur peut etre envoyee a un autre thread.\par
Sync : reference partagee &T peut etre partagee entre threads.\par
\par
13.3 Channels (mpsc)\par
\par
{\f1   use std::sync::mpsc;}\par
{\f1   let (tx, rx) = mpsc::channel();}\par
{\f1   thread::spawn(move || tx.send(42).unwrap());}\par
{\f1   println!("\{\}", rx.recv().unwrap());}\par
\par
13.4 Async / await (1.39+)\par
\par
{\f1   async fn telecharger(url: &str) -> Result<String, Box<dyn Error>> \{}\par
{\f1       let resp = reqwest::get(url).await?.text().await?;}\par
{\f1       Ok(resp)}\par
{\f1   \}}\par
\par
{\f1   #[tokio::main]}\par
{\f1   async fn main() \{}\par
{\f1       let r = telecharger("https://exemple.org").await;}\par
{\f1   \}}\par
\par
Runtimes : tokio (dominant), async-std, smol, embassy (embarque).\par
Primitives : Future trait, .await, async block, join!, select!, spawn.\par
\par
\par
